### Prefab: A Swaying Flower

A flower that oscillates gently (chapter 6) and responds to wind (chapter 5). We'll spawn many.

```scheme
(prefab/define 'flower
  (lambda (x y hue phase)
    (let ((eid (world/spawn x y 'flower)))
      (entity/sprite! eid 'blossom-5)
      (entity/set! eid 'hue hue)
      (entity/set! eid 'phase phase)
      (entity/gravity-scale! eid 0)
      (entity/max-speed! eid 0.5)
      (entity/drag! eid 0.9)
      eid)))

(define (animate-flower eid frame)
  (let* ((phase (entity/get eid 'phase))
         (sway (* 0.3 (dsin (+ (* frame 0.02) phase))))
         (wind-x (car (world/wind)))
         (wind-y (cadr (world/wind))))
    (part/sway eid 'stem sway)
    (entity/accel! eid wind-x wind-y)))

(big-bang
  (on-tick (lambda (state frame)
             (world/step)
             (world/each (lambda (e)
                           (when (eq? (entity/kind e) 'flower)
                             (animate-flower e frame))))
             state))
  (to-draw (lambda (state) #t)))
```

<!-- BUILD: wire as runnable example 16.2; needs prefab/define + world/spawn + world/wind wired in harness -->
<!-- BUILD: ensure part/sway callable (partMotion.js) -->

[VISUAL: Several blossoms swaying in gentle, phase-offset sine waves. When `world/wind!` is called (next example), they lean.]

Each flower has its own `phase` (planted in different moments), so a field of them will ripple asynchronously. `part/sway` (chapter 3) tilts the stem. The flower responds to `world/wind` (chapter 5) by accelerating.

