### Prefab: A Pollinator

A bee that wanders (chapter 10) until it senses nectar, then seeks it (chapter 10 again). We'll give it a utility AI brain (chapter 15) shortly.

```scheme
(prefab/define 'bee
  (lambda (x y)
    (let ((eid (world/spawn x y 'bee)))
      (entity/sprite! eid 'blossom-1)
      (entity/set! eid 'nectar 100)
      (entity/set! eid 'behavior 'wander)
      (entity/max-speed! eid 2.0)
      (entity/gravity-scale! eid 0)
      (ai/max-force! eid 0.5)
      eid)))

(define (animate-bee eid frame)
  (let ((behavior (entity/get eid 'behavior)))
    (cond
      ((eq? behavior 'wander)
       (ai/wander eid 1.0 0.3))
      ((eq? behavior 'seek)
       (let ((target (entity/get eid 'target)))
         (when target
           (ai/seek eid (entity/x target) (entity/y target))))))))

(big-bang
  (on-tick (lambda (state frame)
             (world/step)
             (world/each (lambda (e)
                           (when (eq? (entity/kind e) 'bee)
                             (animate-bee e frame))))
             state))
  (to-draw (lambda (state) #t)))
```

<!-- BUILD: wire as runnable example 16.3; needs ai/wander + ai/seek available in harness -->

[VISUAL: A single bee drifting in a lazy wander pattern, curving smoothly.]

The bee has a `behavior` slot (wander or seek) and a `target` slot (which flower). Right now it only wanders. We'll add decision logic next.

